	Hair resigns from ICC panel  London: Controversial Australian umpire Darrell Hair has resigned from the International Cricket Council (ICC) elite umpires panel, an ICC spokesman said on Friday.  Hair, 55, was removed from the panel for matches involving full member nations after Pakistan forfeited the fourth Test against England at The Oval in 2006 when they were penalised for alleged ball tampering.  He returned to umpiring at the top level this year for two Tests between England and New Zealand.  The ICC spokesman said Hair planned to take up an umpire coaching job in Australia.  
